ons Required Admission Forms Transfer Applicants Application FAQs Apply Application Instructions Required Admission Forms Transfer Applicants Application FAQs Application Instructions Application Instructions  Application Instructions Required Admission Forms Required Admission Forms  Required Admission Forms Transfer Applicants Transfer Applicants  Transfer Applicants Application FAQs Application FAQs  Application FAQs COSTS   AID COSTS   AID  COSTS   AID    CONTACT Admissions Counselors Talk to an Alumnus College Fairs Request Information CONTACT  CONTACT    Admissions Counselors Talk to an Alumnus College Fairs Request Information Admissions Counselors Admissions Counselors  Admissions Counselors Talk to an Alumnus Talk to an Alumnus  Talk to an Alumnus College Fairs College Fairs  College Fairs Request Information Request Information  Request Information Search Search Search  Stories   Video You are here  Home   Experience   Stories   Video   Alumni   Cancer  Just Another Rat Line  Cancer  Just Another Rat Line  January 18  2013 in Alumni  Challenge  by Kate Sean Boyle  91 is an FBI supervisory special agent bomb technician  hazardous devices team leader  and principal firearms instructor for the critical incident response group stationed in Quantico  Va  From the start  he knew VMI was the best way to launch his career  but his VMI education has turned out to be vital to his future in ways he could not have predicted  It was 1994  and Boyle was planning his departure as a first lieutenant in the Army to take up a position with the FBI  when he received some really bad news  he had Hodgkins disease  lymphoma  and his future with the FBI  and any future at all  were in jeopardy  Heading into eight months of chemotherapy  he voiced his feelings at the time   It s just another Rat Line  Boyle found he had the mental stamina to endure chemotherapy  radiation  the fight to get back in shape and complete new agent training  and recurrence   I give full credit to VMI for the mental and physical gymnastics all alumni are exposed to and forced to cope with and manage  says Boyle   VMI taught me that we are capable of so much more than we think we are  and VMI provided that environment to test and prove that fact to all who would become alumni  At the FBI  Boyle has experienced years of success and camaraderie with colleagues who also have a military background and are known for candor  a strong work ethic  effective stress management  and commitment to duty   We also know how to smile and kick back at the end of a tough grind  adds Boyle  At the FBI  he says  they know about VMI and the never say die attitude they re going to get from a VMI grad  Share this entry Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share on Google  Share on Linkedin Share on Tumblr Share on Reddit Share by Mail Stories   Videos Stories   Video Home Stories Slideshows Day in the Life Video Library Admissions Video More About Life at VMI Cadets Academics Athletics Challenge Alumni Faculty and Staff Apply Now Viewbook Links College Fairs FAQs Financial Aid Tuition   Fees Schedule VMI s Institutional Profile Follow  Then lead  Resources VMI CEEB Code  005858 Financial Aid FAFSA Code  003753 Students and their families are encouraged to use a variety of information sources to select a college and major  The State Council of Higher Education for Virginia  SCHEV  provides one such source that is available here  Contact Us VMI Office of Admissions 319 Letcher Avenue Lexington  VA 24450 P  540 464 7211 P  800 767 4207 F  540 464 7746 admissions vmi edu Don t do ordinary  EXPERIENCE VISIT APPLY COSTS   AID CONTACT Stories   Video You are here  Home   Experience   Stories   Video   Alumni   Cancer  Just Another Rat Line Stories   Video You are here  Home   Experience   Stories   Video   Alumni   Cancer  Just Another Rat Line Stories   Video Stories   Video You are here  Home   Experience   Stories   Video   Alumni   Cancer  Just Another Rat Line You are here  Home   Experience   Stories   Video   Alumni   Cancer  Just Another Rat Line You are here You are here Home Home  Experience Experience  Stories   Video Stories   Video  Alumni Alumni  Cancer  Just Another Rat Line Cancer  Just Another Rat Line Cancer  Just Another Rat Line  January 18  2013 in Alumni  Challenge  by Kate Sean Boyle  91 is an FBI supervisory special agent bomb technician  hazardous devices team leader  and principal firearms instructor for the critical incident response group stationed in Quantico  Va  From the start  he knew VMI was the best way to launch his career  but his VMI education has turned out to be vital to his future in ways he could not have predicted  It was 1994  and Boyle was planning his departure as a first lieutenant in the Army to take up a position with the FBI  when he received some really bad news  he had Hodgkins disease  lymphoma  and his future with the FBI  and any future at all  were in jeopardy  Heading into eight months of chemotherapy  he voiced his feelings at the time   It s just another Rat Line  Boyle found he had the mental stamina to endure chemotherapy  radiation  the fight to get back in shape and complete new agent training  and recurrence   I give full credit to VMI for the mental and physical gymnastics all alumni are exposed to and forced to cope with and manage  says Boyle   VMI taught me that we are capable of so much more than we think we are  and VMI provided that environment to test and prove that fact to all who would become alumni  At the FBI  Boyle has experienced years of success and camaraderie with colleagues who also have a military background and are known for candor  a strong work ethic  effective stress management  and commitment to duty   We also know how to smile and kick back at the end of a tough grind  adds Boyle  At the FBI  he says  they know about VMI and the never say die attitude they re going to get from a VMI grad  Share this entry Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share on Google  Share on Linkedin Share on Tumblr Share on Reddit Share by Mail Stories   Videos Stories   Video Home Stories Slideshows Day in the Life Video Library Admissions Video More About Life at VMI Cadets Academics Athletics Challenge Alumni Faculty and Staff Apply Now Cancer  Just Another Rat Line  January 18  2013 in Alumni  Challenge  by Kate Sean Boyle  91 is an FBI supervisory special agent bomb technician  hazardous devices team leader  and principal firearms instructor for the critical incident response group stationed in Quantico  Va  From the start  he knew VMI was the best way to launch his career  but his VMI education has turned out to be vital to his future in ways he could not have predicted  It was 1994  and Boyle was planning his departure as a first lieutenant in the Army to take up a position with the FBI  when he received some really bad news  he had Hodgkins disease  lymphoma  and his future with the FBI  and any future at all  were in jeopardy  Heading into eight months of chemotherapy  he voiced his feelings at the time   It s just another Rat Line  Boyle found he had the mental stamina to endure chemotherapy  radiation  the fight to get back in shape and complete new agent training  and recurrence   I give full credit to VMI for the mental and physical gymnastics all alumni are exposed to and forced to cope with and manage  says Boyle   VMI taught me that we are capable of so much more than we think we are  and VMI provided that environment to test and prove that fact to all who would become alumni  At the FBI  Boyle has experienced years of success and camaraderie with colleagues who also have a military background and are known for candor  a strong work ethic  effective stress management  and commitment to duty   We also know how to smile and kick back at the end of a tough grind  adds Boyle  At the FBI  he says  they know about VMI and the never say die attitude they re going to get from a VMI grad  Share this entry Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share on G